1055845363196874752.text: 9/ Yes, these partnerships can have real business impact. But they can also be a sleazy marketing tactic. DYOR and make your own decisions, but wanted to provide my thoughts as a former enterprise software sales dude. Video rant upcoming as well.

1055845362257313792.text: 8/ It's important for any crypto project, *especially* one with a token in the wild, to understand what impact announcing a partnership with a recognizable company will have. Be clear, be transparent, don't over-exaggerate.

1055845361422614528.text: 7/ The ugly: Some companies, (in my opinion) like Tron, misrepresent "partnerships" by announcing renting cloud servers from Baidu, as a partnership. Using someone's infrastructure and paying them money isn't a partnership, That's being a customer.

1055845357219909633.text: 6/ The ugly: The majority of the crypto population doesn't know the above, and simply sees a major Fortune 500 name like Amazon or Microsoft and jumps to press "BUY, BUY, BUY". Guess when Stratis announced the Microsoft "partnership" on the chart?pic.twitter.com/oAG1hHeLsp

1055845355449933826.text: 5/ The bad: Partner Networks are not exclusive clubs, and should not be represented as such. Amazon added over 10,000 Network Partners alone in 2017. Oracle has over 25,000 partners, Microsoft is even higher.pic.twitter.com/02IDwNp1vb

1055845353294102529.text: 4/ The bad: Joining a Microsoft/Amazon/Oracle/Baidu, etc Partner Network isn't an incredibly difficult task, and representing it as such is unnecessary. Typically, you're looking at a few thousand dollar fee, (provable) functioning software and a few customer references.pic.twitter.com/AbHXhdPSiA

1055845352031576064.text: 3/ The good: Transparency, it's critical. Creating clarity around the nature of a partnership is incredibly important, rather than simply tweeting "ZOMG PARTNERSHIP". A good recent example, @fiebsy with his posthttps://medium.com/0chain/0chain-joins-the-aws-partnership-network-2df0c5fa923c?_branch_match_id=478691444487564178 …

1055845351121473536.text: 2/ The good: There is actual business benefit to something like Stratis/0Chain joining the Azure/AWS partner network in terms of greater software distribution, reaching more potential customers and industry respectability.
